Somersault in a Coffin (Turkish: Tabutta Rvaata) is a 1996 Turkish comedy-drama film, written and directed by Dervi Zaim, about a homeless criminal and car thief. The film, which was released on November 15, 1996(1996-11-15), received awards at several international film festivals including the Golden Orange for best film at the Antalya International Film Festival. Actors Awards Directors Cinematographers Editors Festivals  Producers Production companies Score composers Screenwriters Turkish films by year (category) AZ of Turkish films Pre-1930 1930s 1940s 1950s 1960s 1970s 1980s 1990s 2000s 2010s
